text.section:
A commissioner may not:
act as a broker, agent, attorney, representative, or employee of any person in the person's business dealings with:
Montgomery County;
Prince George's County;
the Washington Suburban Sanitary Commission; or
the Commission;
decide, or participate in, a decision on any matter in which a close business or professional associate has acted as a broker, agent, attorney, representative, or employee of any person or represented private interests before:
Montgomery County;
Prince George's County;
the Washington Suburban Sanitary Commission; or
the Commission; or
represent a private interest or appear in a position of advocacy, other than in the performance of the commissioner's official duties, either in person or through an associate, in any matter or proceeding pending before:
the Montgomery County Council;
the Prince George's County Council;
the Washington Suburban Sanitary Commission;
the Commission;
the Montgomery County Board of Appeals; or
the Prince George's County Board of Appeals.

A commissioner who violates any provision of subsections (b) through (f) of this section is guilty of a misdemeanor and on conviction is subject to:
imprisonment not exceeding 6 months or a fine not exceeding $1,000 or both;
suspension from the Commission or employment not exceeding 6 months;
forfeiture and removal from office; or
any combination of the penalties described in items (1) through (3) of this subsection.
